23 February 2013
----------------

V 1.1
-----

This program creates a solar system and uses Newton's Law of gravitation to animate motion. It allows the user to manipulate and explore the system at will.

Requires:
---------

	*	OpenGL - a graphics library
		-	http://pyopengl.sourceforge.net/
		
	*	numpy - a math library
		-	http://www.numpy.org/
		
Usage:
------

	*	Run the NBodyV_1_1.py file
	
	*	The rar archive contains an executable in the \dist folder for running the program on a Windows PC without Python
	
Features:
---------

	*	Gravitation between multiple astrological objects
	
	*	Adding and subtracting objects from the system
	
	*	Camera rotation about the center of the system with keyboard input
	
	*	Scene traversal with keyboard input
	
	*	Scene traversal with mouse input
	
Future Features:
----------------
		
	*	More variation in mass and density
	
	*	Better collisions (debris)
	
	*	Larger systems
	
	*	Generation of high speed, high mass external astrological objects
	
	*	N number of stars
	
	*	Lighting control
	
	*	Bugfixes for movement
	
	*	Smoother motion
	
Controls:
---------

	*	w: move forward
	
	*	s: move backward
	
	*	a: turn left
	
	*	d: turn right
	
	*	e: turn up
	
	*	q: turn down
	
	*	i: rotate camera up
	
	*	k: rotate camera down
	
	*	j: rotate camera left
	
	*	l: rotate camera right
	
	*	]: add astrological object
	
	*	[: remove astrological object
	
	*	mouse: changes camera facing
	
	*	left click: move forward
	
	*	right click: move backward
	
	*	middle click: stop moving forward or backward

Credits:
--------

